I'm sorry, Chris.
It's hard to accept; hard for the news to sink in, I know .

Are more tests (results) outstanding?
I would want to know if it's gone to his brain and/or bones, as well.
(I haven't heard anything from you that indicates that it has gone to the
brain).

Has he asked about being seen by a radiation oncologist?
A radiation oncologist can help with bone pain.
Maybe shrink some lymph nodes or whatever might be pressing on a nerve causing
the trouble swallowing and talking; maybe even help with the breathing, by
shrinking some of the tumor or lymph nodes.  Someone would have to be there to
help him discuss what can be safely done (in the thoracic area) with RT.

See if anything can be done to help him in the interim, OK?
Hugs from me,
J
