Thanks for the hugs.  I sure need them.  The scans are coming up next.
Today all Robert did was sleep.  But he has to sleep sitting up.  With that
roommate making so much noise, they got him a private room.  I couldn't go
today.  I didn't want to break down in front of him.  They are offering
chemo, but I believe it's only to relieve some of the painful symptoms.  All
of his family are here now.  This is just hell for us.  I will keep you
updated on what's going on with him.  I don't understand him sleeping so
much.  Is this a sign of dying?  When he first went into the hospital 11
days ago he slept normally.  Now it's all the time.  I guess if he has to
leave us I'd rather him do it in his sleep.  I don't want to watch him
suffer.  I certainly don't want to see him not being able to breathe.  His
biggest fear is smothering.  My heart is just broken today.  Love, Chris
